import Mathlib

/-!
If f : U ‚Üí ‚ÑÇ is holomorphic on a domain U ‚äÜ ‚ÑÇ, then f is analytic.
In particular, if U is open and f is complex-differentiable on U, then f is AnalyticOn.
This implies that for each z0 ‚àà U, f has a Taylor series (i.e. is AnalyticAt z0).
-/

theorem holomorphic_on_analytic {U : Set ‚ÑÇ} {f : ‚ÑÇ ‚Üí ‚ÑÇ} (hU : IsOpen U) (h : DifferentiableOn ‚ÑÇ f U) :
  AnalyticOn ‚ÑÇ f U := by
